name: Coastal Kitchen
description: For 25 years, Coastal Kitchen has had the delight of traveling the world, taking you to the far-flung coasts of Sardinia, Venezuela, Hawaii, and many more. With a local spin on regional classics, our unique and regularly changing menus bring new flavors to our Seattle mainstay. Despite our wanderlust spirit, we take pride in the locavore culture  sustainably, locally sourced seafood, meats, and produce. Our fish is wild, our oysters are fresh, and our charm is legendary. We offer 3 Happy Hours daily: 8a  10a (the Dont Judge Me! Happy Hour  for mimosas & Bloody Marys, etc), 3p  6p (including $1.50 oysters, drinks, & snacks), and 9p  close (for that late-night nightcap). Our Happy Hours are honored throughout the restaurant, including our romantic patios. Reservations are accepted and encouraged, but not required! Were open every day, serving Brunch from 8a  3p, mid-day snacks and oysters from 3p  5p, and Dinner from 5p  10p. Tuesday is $1 Oyster Night from 3p  10p!
